    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-02T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-02T05:00:00-05:00" n="311"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.51/448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-02T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1925—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 2—7:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>85. Banking credit contract for 50 million dollars referred to in Department’s
                    telegram No. 63 of May 29, 7 p.m.,<note n="1a" xml:id="d311fn1a">Not
                        printed.</note> was signed last night, and the transaction will be publicly
                    announced to the Parliament by the Minister of Finance this afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
